        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer6048322" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3104968682647531191">This book is endlessly fascinating. Interesting tidbits McGee&apos;s has taught me: raw pineapple will curdle milk, but cooked pineapple will not. Some of our fellow humans will be repulsed by cheese because of an instinctual reaction to fermented foods. See? Fascinating!<br/><br/>McGee&apos;s contains necessary information that you can not get from a recipe on practically every dish and ingredient known to man. This is the kind of book that will sit next to the stove, dog-eared and grease-spattered, eternally usef</span>
  <span id="freeText3104968682647531191" style="display:none">This book is endlessly fascinating. Interesting tidbits McGee's has taught me: raw pineapple will curdle milk, but cooked pineapple will not. Some of our fellow humans will be repulsed by cheese because of an instinctual reaction to fermented foods. See? Fascinating!<br /><br />McGee's contains necessary information that you can not get from a recipe on practically every dish and ingredient known to man. This is the kind of book that will sit next to the stove, dog-eared and grease-spattered, eternally useful, until Personal Chef Robots become fixtures in all of our homes. </span>
