        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2275259724" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3764529861189073565">Alas, it is finished. This book has all the intricate details of everything food. It’s referenced in every other cookbook I’ve read as “the encyclopedia of food.” However, keep it for reference.<br/><br/>It’s too dry to read cover to cover, unless of course you’re fascinated by the lineage of food. Where it started, how it transformed, and how it’s used today.<br/><br/>Also, it’s heavy on chemistry. I suggest to read the appendix first. It’s a refresher crash course. <br/><br/>Overall, way less practical than I hoped for you</span>
  <span id="freeText3764529861189073565" style="display:none">Alas, it is finished. This book has all the intricate details of everything food. It’s referenced in every other cookbook I’ve read as “the encyclopedia of food.” However, keep it for reference.<br /><br />It’s too dry to read cover to cover, unless of course you’re fascinated by the lineage of food. Where it started, how it transformed, and how it’s used today.<br /><br />Also, it’s heavy on chemistry. I suggest to read the appendix first. It’s a refresher crash course. <br /><br />Overall, way less practical than I hoped for your simple home cook.</span>
